cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.RO 

This paper proposes a method to improve the performance of Rolling Horizon Evolutionary Algorithms (RHEA) for real-time game playing by learning a prior in an offline manner. The approach involves training a value network and a policy network, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The use of evolutionary algorithms and game playing also suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Game Theory (cs.GT) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the focus on planning and optimization suggests that the paper could also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
